data.value:
This is a project to visualizes/simulates huffman coding. Huffman coding is a lossless data compression algorithm. The idea is to assign variable-length codes to input characters, lengths of the assigned codes are based on the frequencies of corresponding characters. The most frequent character gets the smallest code and the least frequent character gets the largest code.
In this project both Static and Adaptive Huffman coding has been implemented. When given large data input program may lag due to the nature of it.
